Business Function
Group Technology and Operations (T&amp;O) enables and empowers the bank with an efficient, nimble and resilient infrastructure through a strategic focus on productivity, quality &amp; control, technology, people capability and innovation. In Group T&amp;O, we manage the majority of the Bank's operational processes and inspire to delight our business partners through our multiple banking delivery channels.
About the role
The incumbent will support the security governance and compliance activities in the Bank. The responsibilities of the candidate include ensuring the compliance of the policy architecture to the regulatory requirements, reporting of key metrics and security awareness.
Responsibilities

  Develop, review and update information security policies and standards to meet the compliance and regulatory requirements
  Track and monitor new security regulatory guidelines, and assess the compliance of and impact to the Bank’s security policy architecture
  Work with Line of Business Technology units to ensure compliance to the security legislative requirements and regulatory guidelines
  Assess the security deviations and risk acceptance raised by Business Units/ Support Units
  Review and update cybersecurity risk assessment methodology and conduct cybersecurity risk assessment for critical systems
  Support security updates and reporting to business and support units.
  Support and maintain security awareness and training programs
  Design, produce and analyse IT security metrics for optimal effectiveness and benchmarking

Requirements

  Experienced IS security professional with minimum 8 years of experience preferred in designing and implementing security solutions in a Banking environment
  Familiar with security technology solutions such as but not limited to: IDS, IPS, anti-virus, content filtering, secure email solutions, network sniffing, log analysis, forensics and VPN
  Possess good technical knowledge in various security tools (end-point, network, authentication etc) with comprehensive understanding of regulatory requirements
  Must be solutions-oriented; ability to work with all levels of management and staff; ability to present recommended security controls/processes to key stakeholders
  Proactive, analytical and independent worker with strong organization skills and performance-oriented, demonstrate effectiveness to track and follow up on the assigned projects
  Regional experience is preferred and the ability to travel on need to basis
